      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GALACTIC FORCE (2) resumes for his second campaign. Two runs last time in were okay, both on the Pakenham Synthetic course, but he was in the market each time and should be better for the spell. Expect him to run a good race. MAINMANKASH (1) debuted here on heavy ground over 1100m and got through it well, only being run down late when sent out at $2.80. He gets every chance from the gate here and should get things to suit. SPIRIT OF GAIA (6) ran well first up at Wangaratta to be beaten a head and will be fitter for that which could be the key over her rivals. OTTALAUS (4) resumed having run fairly on debut at Mornington, another one sent out warm in the market. Expect improvement this time around. WEASEL SEA (5) is a Rubick gelding on debut for the Warren yard who can run well.",
